	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Cincin.</placeName> <date>Sept. 5613</date></p>
				<p><sic><addressee>Revd I Leesor</addressee></sic></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I frequently feel an inclination to correspond with your use&#45;<lb/>ful magazine on matters connected with religion and the public procee&#45;<lb/>ding of congregation affairs&#44; which take place within our sphere</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Our object is that such communications be only used when an<lb/> opportunity presents itself.  I notice this perceiving you have an<lb/> agent in this city.  I should much wish to know <sic>throug</sic> <persName>Mr. N<lb/> Matyer</persName> whither such communications will be acceptable.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The <persName>Revd. Dr. Wise</persName> of <placeName>Albany</placeName> has been invited to attend<lb/> at the consecration of our new Synagogue which is to take place<lb/> the <date>14th Sept</date>. Int.  We are also informed that he will be the guest<lb/> of <persName>Mr. Elias Mayors</persName>&#44; this latter gent. and a party are exerting<lb/> their influence to establish a school for the purpose of Educa<lb/>ting the children of our persuasion.  The Laws of God and the duties<lb/> resulting therefrom&#44; in conjunction with the <hi rend="underline">Charterd Talmud</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">Yelodim</hi> of the Baai Jeshurun.  It is <sic>intend</sic> to vest the government of<lb/> the school in the hands of the <persName>Red Dr. Wise</persName>&#44; who is also to be created the<lb/> <sic>the</sic> spiritual Instructor of the joint congregation&#44; Bnai Jeshurun<lb/> and Bnai Israel&#44; and to preach every <date>Sab.</date> alternately in each of<lb/> their Synagogues&#44; the move is a good one&#44; such a union would mater<lb/>ialy lighten expenses&#44; but <persName>Dr. Wise</persName> has not the shadow of a chance<lb/> of ever being <sic>allowd</sic> to deliver a <hi rend="underline">single</hi> discourse in our Synagogue&#44;<lb/> much more to have an <sic>offical</sic> appointment we have great reason<lb/> to believe that the Dr. will be the successor of the <persName>Rd I. Rosenfelt</persName> with<lb/> the K. K. B. J. their principal leaders declare that <persName>Dr. Wise</persName> has<lb/> done more good already in <placeName>Albany</placeName> than any man in this country.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">yours very Respy</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">Saml. Bruel</persName></p>
				<p>K.K.B I. The Annual Election took place this<lb/> Evening&#44; the following persons were chosen to serve for one year<lb/> <persName>Ferdinand Milias</persName> Parnass. <persName>N. Maltzer</persName> <persName>zab Zedokah</persName>&#44; <persName role="author">S. Bruel</persName> <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> <persName>Isaac Wolf</persName> Treasurer&#44; <persName>Jospht.</persName> Secy.</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>Sept. 4th</date></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>N. B</p>
				<p>We have never had so full an attendance at an Election&#44; as on this <sic>ocasion</sic><lb/> the three candidates&#58; <persName>J Jonas</persName>&#44; <persName>Elias Mayer</persName> &#38; <persName>T Milions</persName> were busily engaged<lb/> for some time pass&#39; &#40;through their funds&#41; canvasing.  The officers <sic>ellected</sic><lb/> are popular persons.  The election of this Earning decides the fate of <persName>Dr.<lb/> Wise</persName> with our congregation</p>
		</body>
